I’ve been a fan of Vikram Bhatt’s movies. He made really good movies like Raaz, Shaapit, 1920, haunted 3D, Awara pagal deewana, ghulam and also produced a brilliant horror flick “horror story” but this trailer doesn’t match up to the level of those movies. Cinematography looks bad, like really really bad. It looks like they’ve used an Instagram filter, I mean it looks cheap. I’ve seen better horror movie trailers. For instance, 1920 London trailer was good, though the movie turned out to be very bad. Vikram Bhatt’s last great movie was Haunted 3D. He may have made money in Raaz 3 but it wasn’t a great horror movie. I’m being honest, I’m sorry. I believe if he had a better cast in Shaapit, it would be a super hit but never mind. Just like a writer’s block, it seems like Vikram is also suffering from a director’s block. He seems to be have run out of ideas, he used to be a great horror director but this trailer for me is a big disappointment. I really didn’t like it. He must understand that now, the works for horror flicks is not the same like that of early 2000’s. Conjuring universe has turned it upside down. With movies like IT, The curse of La llorana, Annabelle 2 and 3, conjuring 1 and 2, lights out and exorcism of Emily rose, the world has entered into a new era of horror and this Ghost movie trailer looks like that of late 90’s one. It’s too bad. I’m sorry Vikram. I’ve been a fan of you, I was 8 yo when Raaz was released, it scared the shit out of me, I was in 12th when Shaapit was released, I loved watching it in cinema, I also loved haunted 3D but this trailer has disappointed me. I’m sorry. You could be the James Wan of Bollywood if you want to but it seems like you don’t want to.
